<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="503" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,618,1653]" box="[199,1380,798,825]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,798,824]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Description:</emphasis>
Larva: Body length 
<quantity box="[579,668,798,825]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="503" unit="mm" value="9.8">9.8 mm</quantity>
; length of cerci 
<quantity box="[848,951,798,825]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.04" pageId="4" pageNumber="503" unit="mm" value="10.4">10.4 mm</quantity>
. Body generally dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[1284,1367,798,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 18. Dorsal view; 19. Abdomen ventral view; 20. Abdomen dorsal view; 21. Posterior margin of abdominal terga V; 22. Antenna; 23 Labrum; 24. Hypopharynx." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042530/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,618,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,272,834,860]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Head:</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[371,462,834,861]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="503" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[550,641,834,861]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="503" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
; light brown (
<figureCitation box="[806,892,834,860]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 18. Dorsal view; 19. Abdomen ventral view; 20. Abdomen dorsal view; 21. Posterior margin of abdominal terga V; 22. Antenna; 23 Labrum; 24. Hypopharynx." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042530/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
); subquadrangular; anterior and lateral margins convex, with rows of hair-like setae directed anteriorly. Compound eyes black. Antennae with scape, pedicels and flagella light brown (
<figureCitation box="[386,470,906,932]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 18. Dorsal view; 19. Abdomen ventral view; 20. Abdomen dorsal view; 21. Posterior margin of abdominal terga V; 22. Antenna; 23 Labrum; 24. Hypopharynx." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042530/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Labrum brown with deep median notch on anterior margin, long hair-like setae laterally (
<figureCitation box="[208,292,942,968]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 18. Dorsal view; 19. Abdomen ventral view; 20. Abdomen dorsal view; 21. Posterior margin of abdominal terga V; 22. Antenna; 23 Labrum; 24. Hypopharynx." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042530/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Hypopharynx as in 
<figureCitation box="[529,610,942,968]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 18. Dorsal view; 19. Abdomen ventral view; 20. Abdomen dorsal view; 21. Posterior margin of abdominal terga V; 22. Antenna; 23 Labrum; 24. Hypopharynx." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042530/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
. Mandibles without scattered setae along the molar area; incisors serrated, outer incisor longer than inner incisor (
<figureCitation box="[589,720,978,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–34" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1384,1408]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,182,1356]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[151,1436,181,1360]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25–34. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 25. Left mandible; 26. Right mandible; 27. Maxilla; 28. Labium; 29. Foreleg; 30. Midleg; 31. Hindleg; 31a. Dorsal surface of femur; 32. Claw; 33. Gill I; 34. Gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042532/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Figs 25–26</figureCitation>
). Maxilla as in 
<figureCitation box="[893,975,978,1004]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–34" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1384,1408]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,182,1356]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[151,1436,181,1360]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25–34. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 25. Left mandible; 26. Right mandible; 27. Maxilla; 28. Labium; 29. Foreleg; 30. Midleg; 31. Hindleg; 31a. Dorsal surface of femur; 32. Claw; 33. Gill I; 34. Gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042532/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
. Labium (
<figureCitation box="[1089,1170,978,1004]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–34" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1384,1408]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,182,1356]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[151,1436,181,1360]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25–34. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 25. Left mandible; 26. Right mandible; 27. Maxilla; 28. Labium; 29. Foreleg; 30. Midleg; 31. Hindleg; 31a. Dorsal surface of femur; 32. Claw; 33. Gill I; 34. Gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042532/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) as in the previous species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,618,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,297,1050,1076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Thorax:</emphasis>
Pronotum pale brown with indistinct band in middle and pair of dark spots; mesonotum brown (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 18. Dorsal view; 19. Abdomen ventral view; 20. Abdomen dorsal view; 21. Posterior margin of abdominal terga V; 22. Antenna; 23 Labrum; 24. Hypopharynx." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042530/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Legs (
<figureCitation box="[276,409,1086,1112]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–34" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1384,1408]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,182,1356]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[151,1436,181,1360]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25–34. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 25. Left mandible; 26. Right mandible; 27. Maxilla; 28. Labium; 29. Foreleg; 30. Midleg; 31. Hindleg; 31a. Dorsal surface of femur; 32. Claw; 33. Gill I; 34. Gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042532/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Figs 29–31</figureCitation>
): Femora light brown, hypodermal spot on middle, outer margin with long setae and dark brown maculae medially; distal end with blunt spine; dorsal surface with scattered stout short thickened setae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 25–34" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1384,1408]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,182,1356]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[151,1436,181,1360]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25–34. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 25. Left mandible; 26. Right mandible; 27. Maxilla; 28. Labium; 29. Foreleg; 30. Midleg; 31. Hindleg; 31a. Dorsal surface of femur; 32. Claw; 33. Gill I; 34. Gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042532/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 31a</figureCitation>
); tibia pale brown with long hair-like setae on outer margin; claw with 3 small denticles (
<figureCitation box="[1196,1280,1158,1184]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–34" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1384,1408]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,182,1356]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[151,1436,181,1360]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25–34. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 25. Left mandible; 26. Right mandible; 27. Maxilla; 28. Labium; 29. Foreleg; 30. Midleg; 31. Hindleg; 31a. Dorsal surface of femur; 32. Claw; 33. Gill I; 34. Gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042532/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,618,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,1194,1220]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Abdominal terga light brown, terga II–IX with pair of short submedian spines (
<figureCitation box="[1209,1338,1194,1220]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 18. Dorsal view; 19. Abdomen ventral view; 20. Abdomen dorsal view; 21. Posterior margin of abdominal terga V; 22. Antenna; 23 Labrum; 24. Hypopharynx." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042530/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Figs 18, 20</figureCitation>
); tergum II yellowish, terga III and IV with indistinct pale patches on middle, terga V–VIII with light middle band; terga II–IX with small setae along midline (
<figureCitation box="[587,672,1266,1292]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 18. Dorsal view; 19. Abdomen ventral view; 20. Abdomen dorsal view; 21. Posterior margin of abdominal terga V; 22. Antenna; 23 Labrum; 24. Hypopharynx." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042530/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
); segments II–VII with long postero-lateral extensions; sterna light yellowish without markings (
<figureCitation box="[479,562,1302,1328]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 18. Dorsal view; 19. Abdomen ventral view; 20. Abdomen dorsal view; 21. Posterior margin of abdominal terga V; 22. Antenna; 23 Labrum; 24. Hypopharynx." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042530/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). Gill I triangular (
<figureCitation box="[774,857,1302,1328]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–34" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1384,1408]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,182,1356]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[151,1436,181,1360]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25–34. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 25. Left mandible; 26. Right mandible; 27. Maxilla; 28. Labium; 29. Foreleg; 30. Midleg; 31. Hindleg; 31a. Dorsal surface of femur; 32. Claw; 33. Gill I; 34. Gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042532/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
); gills II–VII oval (
<figureCitation box="[1075,1159,1302,1328]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–34" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1384,1408]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,182,1356]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[151,1436,181,1360]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25–34. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 25. Left mandible; 26. Right mandible; 27. Maxilla; 28. Labium; 29. Foreleg; 30. Midleg; 31. Hindleg; 31a. Dorsal surface of femur; 32. Claw; 33. Gill I; 34. Gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042532/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). Cerci with row of hairlike setae dorsally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="503" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,618,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1374,1400]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The larva of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Braasch &amp; Soldan" authorityYear="1979" box="[469,730,1374,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifurcatus" subGenus="Epeorus">
<emphasis box="[469,562,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Epeorus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[577,602,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">E.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[617,730,1374,1400]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">bifurcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other species of this genus by the following combination of characters: (i) posterior margin of abdominal terga II–IX with pair of short submedian spines (
<figureCitation box="[159,312,1446,1472]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 18. Dorsal view; 19. Abdomen ventral view; 20. Abdomen dorsal view; 21. Posterior margin of abdominal terga V; 22. Antenna; 23 Labrum; 24. Hypopharynx." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042530/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Figs 18 &amp; 20</figureCitation>
); terga II–IX with small setae along midline (
<figureCitation box="[821,904,1446,1472]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 18. Dorsal view; 19. Abdomen ventral view; 20. Abdomen dorsal view; 21. Posterior margin of abdominal terga V; 22. Antenna; 23 Labrum; 24. Hypopharynx." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042530/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
); and (iii) gill I larger than others (
<figureCitation box="[1293,1376,1446,1472]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–34" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1384,1408]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,182,1356]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[151,1436,181,1360]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25–34. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) bifurcatus 25. Left mandible; 26. Right mandible; 27. Maxilla; 28. Labium; 29. Foreleg; 30. Midleg; 31. Hindleg; 31a. Dorsal surface of femur; 32. Claw; 33. Gill I; 34. Gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042532/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,927,1482,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,618,1653]" box="[199,927,1482,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,355,1482,1508]" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[361,459,1482,1508]" name="Vietnam" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[469,569,1482,1508]" name="Thailand" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">Thailand</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[623,681,1482,1508]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="503">India</collectingCountry>
